export function is<T>(input: T): input is T;
export function is<T>(input: unknown): input is T;
Tests a value type.When you need to test an instance type, just call typia.is<T>() function.If the input value is following type T, true value would be returned. Otherwise, false would be returned.
AOT compliation
If you'd used other competitive validator libraries like ajv or class-validator, you may found that typia does not require any extra schema definition. If you have not experienced them, I can sure that you may get shocked after reading below extra schema definition files.
ajv requires JSON schema definition.
class-validator requires DTO class with decorator function calls.
